  A_i =  A\text{ wins on the } i^{\rm th}\text{ flip; where }i\text { is odd}. 
P(A_i) =\Bigl({1\over2}\Bigr)^{i-1}\cdot{1\over2} =\Bigl({1\over2}\Bigr)^i. 
A
 \sum_{i \text{ odd}} P(A_i)= \sum_{i \text { odd}} \Bigl({1\over 2}\Bigr)^i. 
 \sum_{i \text { odd}} \Bigl({1\over 2}\Bigr)^i= \sum_{i =0}^{\infty} \Bigl({1\over 2}\Bigr)^{2i+1}= {1\over 2}\sum_{i =0}^{\infty} \Bigl({1\over 4}\Bigr)^{ i }={1\over2}\cdot{4\over3}=2/3.    
