\sum_{k=0}^{\infty}2^{-(2k+1)}=(1/2)(1/(1-1/4))=2/3
\begin{align} P(\text{A winning}) &= P(\text{A winning in his first toss or } \mathrm{A_1} \text{ or } \mathrm{A_2} \text{ or } \ldots)\\ &= P(\text{A winning in his first toss}) + P(\mathrm{A_1}) + P(\mathrm{A_2}) + \dots\\ &= 0.5 + (0.5)(0.5)(0.5) + (0.5)(0.5)(0.5)(0.5)(0.5) + \dots \\ &=0.5 + (0.5)^3 + (0.5)^5 + .........\\ &= \frac{0.5}{1 - 0.25} = \frac{0.5}{0.75} = \frac{50}{75} = \frac{2}{3}\\ \end{align}
